quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  5,65,"And had the People of the Scripture attained faith and been mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>, We would surely have remitted their evil deeds and entered them into the Gardens of Bliss."
  5,66,"And had they established the Torah and the Gospel and what was sent down to them from their Lord, they would surely have eaten from above them and from beneath their feet{1}. Among them is a moderate community, but<i class=""s"">(regarding) </i>many of them—evil is what they do.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘legs’.
  5,67,"O Messenger, proclaim what was sent down to you from your Lord; but if you do not, then you will not have proclaimed <span class=""h"">His message<sup foot_note=""79943"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, for Allah safeguards you from mankind. Indeed, Allah does not guide the denying people."
  5,68,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “O People of the Scripture, you have no basis until you establish the Torah and the Gospel and what was sent down to you from your Lord.” But most surely what was sent down to you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>from your Lord will increase many of them in exceeding all limits and in denial, so do not be sorry for the denying people."
  5,69,"Indeed, those who have attained faith and those who have Judaized and the Sabians and the Christians—whoever has attained faith in Allah and the Last Day and has acted righteously—then <span class=""h"">no fear<sup foot_note=""79944"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">shall be</span>upon them{2}, nor shall they grieve.",footnotes:2:A grammatical shift from singular to plural.
  5,70,"We very truly took a pledge from the Children of Israel and We sent to them messengers; whenever a messenger came to them with what their<i class=""s"">(inner) </i>selves did not desire, one group they disbelieved, and another group they kill{1}.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense. Using present tense for an old practice emphasizes that it was a tradition frequently practiced.
